{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-single-rating-js","path":"/story-time-how-the-hair-industry-saved-and-raised-curl-specialist-raquel-noriko","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"7014244d-d8a1-5f1d-aa74-eb750138a591","html":"<p>Raquel Noriko is a curly hair specialist based in Maui, HI. Her passion for people as well as curly hair is seen through her intuitive approach and cutting style to each client and their needs. </p>\n<p>\"I help women embrace their natural hair effortlessly one curly head at a time. I believe that our confidence as women starts with embracing ourselves at our core.  For us naturally curly hair women, that begins with our hair.\" - Raquel Noriko  </p>\n<p><em>Check out a bit of her story as a curly hair specialist</em> ⬇️ </p>\n<p>\"At 16 I knew I wanted to be in the hair industry and at the age of 18, after high school, I went straight into beauty school, graduating with my license at 19 years old. I went all in and started working at a salon in my hometown as an assistant, I learned all there was to know about hair that beauty school hadn’t taught me.  </p>\n<p>I say the salon and industry raised me because home life for me was very isolating, dark, and confusing from the young age of 15-18. My mom checked out when I was 15 and I was around women that literally in my book raised me from the age of 19 when I entered the salon to work, while hearing their stories day in and day out from either in the chair or at the shampoo bowl. The community I built while in there was a saving grace. You are exposed to a lot in the salon world lol. I learned valuable lessons from men and women sitting in the chair hearing them spill their life!   </p>\n<p>When I became my own stylist I chose to really dedicate my craft to naturally curly hair since I had it and had grown up around it. I started to wear my natural hair after years of straightening and damaging my hair. When I finished assisting I decided to solely specialize in curly hair because of the knowledge of my natural curls and continued education. I’m cutting and coloring. It’s taken me very far in my career and has advanced it tremendously. I have been able to travel around the world with this specialty and meet tons of beautiful people because of it. It has sustained me and built a clientele in Los Angeles where I am originally from to live on the island of Maui and build my clientele out here for the last 5 years. It has been good to me. The only reason it has is that it’s where my true passion lies. I see my lineage in this craft and career of mine every day that a curly head sits in my chair but even more so out here on the Hawaiian islands. There’s no truer connection than that!\"  </p>\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" data-instgrm-permalink=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/CRcGrlyNm28/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" data-instgrm-version=\"13\" style=\" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:540px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);\"><div style=\"padding:16px;\"> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/CRcGrlyNm28/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" style=\" background:#FFFFFF; line-height:0; padding:0 0; text-align:center; text-decoration:none; width:100%;\" target=\"_blank\"> <div style=\" display: flex; flex-direction: row; align-items: center;\"> <div style=\"background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 50%; flex-grow: 0; height: 40px; margin-right: 14px; width: 40px;\"></div> <div style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: column; flex-grow: 1; justify-content: center;\"> <div style=\" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px; width: 100px;\"></div> <div style=\" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; width: 60px;\"></div></div></div><div style=\"padding: 19% 0